            "rationale": "Reviewer's F5 cited sec 9.3:850 and sec 13.9:1040 ('UUIDv5 derived from the seed and the operation context') with no namespace UUID and no canonical name encoding. Critic verified against RFC 4122 sec 4.3 (namespace UUID is mandatory for UUIDv5) and confirmed two RFC-conformant implementations will diverge from the same seed. NFR-013 byte-identicality is unachievable in ecm:deterministic mode until: (a) a normative namespace UUID is fixed, (b) the operation-context field set is enumerated, (c) the canonical-name byte encoding is specified.",
            "trace": {
              "reviewer_finding_id": "F5",
              "critic_verdict_id": "F5"
            }
          },
          {
            "id": "I6",
            "title": "SPEC sec 4.1 five-layer model is unreconciled with ARCHITECTURE.md / CLAUDE.md three-layer model enforced by npm run test:purity",
