              "critic_verdict_id": "F15"
            }
          },
          {
            "id": "I16",
            "title": "SPEC.md carries no RFC 2119 conformance declaration despite pervasive lowercase normative keywords",
            "consensus": "both_agree",
            "resolution": "accept_reviewer",
            "severity": "minor",
            "rationale": "Reviewer's F16 cited the absence of RFC 2119 boilerplate in SPEC.md while ARCHITECTURE.md:9, COMPUTATION_MODEL.md sec 1:5, and CLAUDE.md preamble all carry it. Critic confirmed and added evidence (SPEC.md:287 'must include this @context'; SPEC.md:1236 'block save by default'). Normative force is formally ambiguous; reviewers cannot reject an implementation that interprets lowercase 'must' as 'should'.",
            "trace": {
