          {
            "id": "I20",
            "title": "Canvas-layout nested arrays (ecm:nodes, ecm:edges) have no canonical ordering rule; NFR-012/NFR-013 broken for every UI-edited project",
            "consensus": "critic_only",
            "resolution": "accept_critic",
            "severity": "major",
            "rationale": "Critic's M2 found that sec 5.3 rule 4:327-336 enumerates lexicographic id-ordering only for the eight top-level array keys. The ecm:nodes and ecm:edges arrays inside each ecm:CanvasLayout (sec 5.11:530-554) have neither id-bearing fields (CanvasNode keys on ecm:instanceIri; CanvasEdge keys on ecm:relationId) nor an ordering rule. Two implementations producing the same set of canvas nodes will canonicalize them in arbitrary orders, breaking NFR-012 (round-trip) and NFR-013 (cross-implementation byte-identity) for effectively every UI-edited project. Reviewer did not surface this defect. Fix requires adding a normative ordering key (recommend ecm:instanceIri for nodes, ecm:relationId for edges) to sec 5.3 rule 4.",
            "trace": {
              "critic_missed_id": "M2"
            }
          },
          {
            "id": "I21",
            "title": "Canonical form of @type for single-valued entities is undefined; scalar-vs-single-element-array divergence breaks NFR-013",
            "consensus": "critic_only",
            "resolution": "accept_critic",
            "severity": "major",
            "rationale": "Critic's M3 cited sec 5.4:345 (project root emits type as a lexicographically-sorted array even when it has two values) versus sec 5.7:452, sec 5.8:473, sec 5.9:493 (scalar 'type': 'owl:Class'). Sec 5.3:325-336 is silent on which form is canonical. JSON-LD compaction permits either. Two implementations canonicalizing the same logical project \u00e2\u20ac\u201d one always-array, one always-scalar-when-single \u00e2\u20ac\u201d produce different bytes for every term, instance, and assertion. NFR-013 is unverifiable. Reviewer missed this entirely. Fix requires sec 5.3 to mandate one form (recommend: always scalar for single, always array for multi, with deterministic sort).",
            "trace": {
              "critic_missed_id": "M3"
            }
          },
          {
            "id": "I22",
            "title": "Internal contradiction between sec 5.14 Project TBox using rdfs:domain/range and sec 7.5 deferring domain/range to v0.4",
            "consensus": "critic_only",
            "resolution": "accept_critic",
            "severity": "major",
            "rationale": "Critic's M4 found sec 5.14:626-629 declares ecm:isSerializationOf with rdfs:domain ecm:Serialization; rdfs:range iao:OntologyDesignPattern, while sec 7.5:780-782 states 'The MVP does not model rdfs:domain / rdfs:range as first-class TBox fields. A user who needs them can declare them via project-created assertions in v0.4. Documented as a known gap.' The spec's own normative TBox uses domain/range while declaring domain/range is unmodeled. Implementer cannot tell whether to emit them. Either sec 7.5 must be revised to exclude the Project TBox, or sec 5.14 must avoid rdfs:domain/range. Reviewer did not catch this.",
            "trace": {
              "critic_missed_id": "M4"
            }
          },
          {
            "id": "I23",
            "title": "Sec 5.11 adapter-state 'discard without error' rule is undefined and conflicts with NFR-012 round-trip",
            "consensus": "critic_only",
            "resolution": "accept_critic",
            "severity": "major",
            "rationale": "Critic's M5 cited sec 5.11:556 ('Library-specific state may live under a namespaced adapter field if needed (e.g., ecm:adapterState/reactflow), and must be discarded by other implementations without error.') against sec 5.3:338 (lossless round-trip = serialize(parse(file)) == file bytewise) and NFR-012:1421. The spec does not say whether 'discard without error' means (a) silently strip on read, (b) preserve through round-trip but ignore semantically, or (c) reject at schema boundary. Cross-implementation editing of any layout that touches adapter state is therefore broken. Reviewer missed this. Fix MUST specify preserve-through-round-trip semantics (option b) or NFR-012 must be qualified to exclude foreign adapter state.",
            "trace": {
              "critic_missed_id": "M5"
            }
          },
          {
            "id": "I24",
