            "consensus": "critic_only",
            "resolution": "accept_critic",
            "severity": "advisory",
            "rationale": "Critic's M9 cited sec 24:1567-1576 (three MVP starters, four advanced starters \u00e2\u20ac\u201d none with declared iao:isAbout) versus sec 22 step 27:1513 ('Load at least three starter examples (each with its own declared iao:isAbout)') and sec 31 DoD #1:1766 (project must declare iao:isAbout). The spec leaves implementers to invent realist anchors for canonical starter content; two compliant implementations may ship the same starter with different anchor IRIs and therefore different canonical bytes against the sec 21.1:1442-1446 golden-file suite. Reviewer missed this. Each starter's realist anchor must be normatively pinned.",
