            "rationale": "The reviewer identified a two-way ownership overlap: Phase 1 scope commits a 'golden-file \u00e2\u20ac\u00a6 conformance' test harness citing \u00c2\u00a721.1, and Phase 4 scope adds 'Conformance goldens added for every export format, byte-compared in CI (\u00c2\u00a721.1, NFR-013)' \u00e2\u20ac\u201d both citing \u00c2\u00a721.1 without specifying which fixture inputs or output formats belong to each phase. The critic confirmed this and materially widened the scope: Phase 6 adds a third distinct layer ('Per-starter committed golden files: project.jsonld, graph.ttl, graph.nt, graph.jsonld, default.mmd, model-summary.md (\u00c2\u00a721.1)'). All three phases cite \u00c2\u00a721.1 without specifying which fixture inputs drive each phase's golden set or how the phases differ. The critic also sharpened the argument: because Phase 1 is NOT-in-scope for ZIP packaging, Phase 4's only unambiguously new golden artifact may be manifest.jsonld \u00e2\u20ac\u201d but the ROADMAP says 'every export format.' The source artifact confirms all cited scope lines exactly as reported.",
