            "rationale": "I8 (minor, resolution: merge): The parenthetical '(a minimal Turtle parser is sufficient here for emitter golden-file tests)' justifies a Phase 1 component against a test type that does not require a parser. Emitter golden-file tests compare byte output against a committed file; the \u00c2\u00a717.6 parse-cleanly check that actually requires a parser is explicitly Phase 4 scope. The parenthetical creates a scoped-but-unanchored deliverable with no FR reference. Removing it eliminates the confusion without touching any other scope.",
