        "instructions": [
          "STEP 1: Use your Read tool to inspect the current state of each of the three target files. The files currently contain mojibake bytes; you will see them as the corrupted character sequences.",
          "STEP 2: For each file, identify each mojibake instance. The known mojibake patterns to replace are:",
          "  - 0xC3 0x82 0xC2 0xA7 (visible as the two-character mojibake sequence) should become 0xC2 0xA7 (the section sign U+00A7).",
          "  - 0xC3 0xA2 0xE2 0x82 0xAC 0xE2 0x80 0x9C (visible as the three-character mojibake sequence) should become 0xE2 0x80 0x94 (the em-dash U+2014).",
          "  - 0xC3 0xA2 0xE2 0x80 0xA0 0xC2 0xB2 (visible as another three-character mojibake sequence) should become 0xE2 0x80 0x99 (the right single quotation mark U+2019).",
          "  - 0xC3 0xA2 0xE2 0x80 0xA0 0xC2 0xB4 (visible as another three-character mojibake sequence) should become 0xE2 0x86 0x92 (the rightwards arrow U+2192).",
          "  - Use the Read tool's actual byte-level view to identify each instance.",
          "STEP 3: For EACH affected file, emit ONE change with mode=edit. Set 'before' to a substring that uniquely identifies the location AND contains the mojibake-bearing bytes EXACTLY as they appear on disk. Set 'after' to the same substring with the mojibake replaced by the proper Unicode equivalents.",
          "STEP 4: To avoid re-introducing mojibake in your own JSON output: emit non-ASCII characters using Unicode escape sequences (\\u00a7 for the section sign, \\u2014 for the em-dash, \\u2019 for the right single quotation mark, \\u2192 for the rightwards arrow). Do not emit the raw non-ASCII bytes in your JSON output.",
          "STEP 5: Make 'before' snippets large enough to be UNIQUE in the target file (the applier requires exactly-one match). Multiple mojibake instances in one file may need ONE encompassing change with a large before/after pair OR multiple smaller changes each with a uniquely-anchored before.",
          "STEP 6: Do NOT change runtime behavior. The mojibake is in comments and ADR body text only. The TypeScript code logic and the ADR-006 decision/context/consequences semantics must be preserved exactly."
