        "open_questions": [
          "ONTOLOGY FILE REVIEW REQUIRED (agent contract section 8): src/tbox/project-tbox.ttl is a .ttl file. Orchestrator should queue a semantic-sme review task before the apply step runs. The review is expected to be straightforward (content is verbatim from SPEC section 5.14) but is required by contract.",
          "N3.js version: proposal uses ^1.21.0 as an estimate for a recent stable release. Operator should verify the exact latest stable version on npm (npm info n3 version) before applying C4, and adjust if ^1.21.0 does not resolve.",
          "N3.js NodeNext import compatibility: if `import { Parser } from 'n3'` fails TypeScript type resolution under moduleResolution: NodeNext (e.g., N3.js exports field lacks a 'types' condition), the fallback is: `import n3Pkg from 'n3'; const { Parser } = n3Pkg as typeof import('n3');` with the import line annotated. This does not affect runtime behavior under Node 22 since CJS-from-ESM named imports work for well-behaved CJS modules.",
          "UTF-8 BOM on new .ttl file: the applier writes UTF-8 BOM on new files by default. BOM (0xEF 0xBB 0xBF) is accepted by N3.js (AC1 will pass), but may cause issues with stricter third-party Turtle parsers or golden-file byte comparison when AC3 ships. If BOM causes AC3 failures, the applier's BOM behavior for .ttl files needs an exception or the golden file must be generated from the BOM-prefixed file.",
          "rdfs:domain and rdfs:range in getProjectTBoxNodes(): currently plain compact IRI strings (e.g., 'ecm:Serialization'). VMP_CONTEXT (SPEC section 5.2) does not declare these predicates with '@type': '@id', so a JSON-LD processor will treat their values as plain strings, not IRI references. Task 1.4 (semantic projection) must either extend VMP_CONTEXT with entries for rdfs:domain and rdfs:range, or use explicit value objects ({ '@id': '...' }) when inserting TBox nodes into @graph. Confirm the expected interface shape before task 1.4 ships.",
          "Golden file directory: IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md section 1.2 AC3 references test/golden/project-tbox.ttl (test/, not tests/). Recon finding F18 flags this as a known ambiguity. AC3 is deferred, but the directory name must be resolved before any golden-file task ships."
        ],
        "summary": "Four changes implement IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md section 1.2 (Project TBox Bundle): (C1) src/tbox/project-tbox.ttl with the verbatim SPEC section 5.14 Turtle block; (C2) src/tbox/index.ts exporting getProjectTBoxTurtle(): string and getProjectTBoxNodes(): object[], both pure functions with no I/O; (C3) tests/tbox-bundle.test.ts implementing AC1 (N3.js parse, zero errors) and AC2 (set-equality on 5 declarations by IRI and property) with AC3 as a deferred stub, following the vmp-serializer.test.ts hand-rolled pattern exactly; (C4) package.json devDependency addition of n3 ^1.21.0. No src/kernel/ files are modified. tsconfig files require no changes (recon F11). The test is auto-discovered by run-tests.ts without changes (recon F10). Ontology file open_question flagged for semantic-sme routing per agent contract.",
