      "outputs": {
        "ruling": "ratified",
        "editorial_verdict": "substantive",
        "editorial_verdict_reason": "The proposal introduces a new source module (src/tbox/), a new test file (tests/tbox-bundle.test.ts), and a new devDependency (n3 ^1.21.0) \u00e2\u20ac\u201d none of which are typo fixes, formatting corrections, terminology tightening, or citation-format updates.",
        "rationale": "Reconnaissance (urn:fnsr:task:087-recon-tbox-bundle) is present in UPSTREAM and adequate. The developer's four changes address all reconnaissance findings without structural defect.\n\n**SPEC \u00c2\u00a75.14 axiom fidelity (C1 + C2):** The Turtle block in src/tbox/project-tbox.ttl and the embedded PROJECT_TBOX_TURTLE constant in src/tbox/index.ts are byte-for-byte identical to the normative \u00c2\u00a75.14 block in SPEC.md lines 601\u00e2\u20ac\u201c635, confirmed by direct file comparison. All five named entities are present with correct rdf:type, rdfs:subClassOf, rdfs:domain, and rdfs:range assertions.\n\n**AC1 and AC2 test coverage (C3):** tests/tbox-bundle.test.ts implements AC1 (N3.js Parser.parse returns >0 quads with zero errors) and AC2 (five separate try/catch blocks verifying full-IRI triples for all five \u00c2\u00a75.14 declarations by subject, predicate, and object IRIs). Additional getProjectTBoxNodes() shape checks (array length == 5; compact-IRI id set-equality) round out the contract. The developer's self-reported test count of 9 passes (AC1\u00c3\u20141 + AC2\u00c3\u20145 + nodes-shape\u00c3\u20142 + AC3-stub\u00c3\u20141) is arithmetically correct. AC3 (golden-file byte-equality) is deferred with a labeled stub per vmp-serializer.test.ts precedent and OED-313 gate \u00e2\u20ac\u201d this is correct.\n\n**Test infrastructure pattern conformance:** The hand-rolled runner pattern (no framework, try/catch, pass()/fail() with \\u2713/\\u2717 Unicode markers, node:assert, process.exit(1) on failure) precisely mirrors tests/vmp-serializer.test.ts. No changes to run-tests.ts or either tsconfig are required; reconnaissance findings F10 and F11 confirm auto-discovery and auto-include.\n\n**Kernel purity invariant:** src/tbox/index.ts (C2) has zero import statements. It contains only a string constant and two pure exported functions. It cannot violate layer boundaries because it imports nothing. The npm run test:purity path is unaffected: ensure-kernel-purity.ts scans only dist-tests/src/kernel/ and src/tbox/ is not in scope.\n\n**devDependency classification (C4):** n3 is added to devDependencies only, not dependencies. No src/ file imports from n3; the import appears exclusively in tests/tbox-bundle.test.ts. CLAUDE.md \u00c2\u00a76 explicitly permits devDependency additions without Human Orchestrator approval ('devDependencies are acceptable'). The developer's reading of CLAUDE.md \u00c2\u00a76 is correct; the fast-check deferral precedent (recon F19) predates or misapplied that rule and does not bind this decision.\n\n**VMP_CONTEXT id/type alias consistency:** src/kernel/canonicalize.ts VMP_CONTEXT declares `id: '@id'` and `type: '@type'` (lines 74\u00e2\u20ac\u201c75), so the developer's use of compact `id` and `type` keys in getProjectTBoxNodes() is coherent with the context. `rdfs:subClassOf` is declared `{ '@type': '@id', '@container': '@set' }` in VMP_CONTEXT; the developer correctly uses array values for rdfs:subClassOf fields.\n\n**Outstanding operational risks (not blocking):** (1) rdfs:domain and rdfs:range are not in VMP_CONTEXT as `'@type': '@id'`; task 1.4 must extend VMP_CONTEXT before getProjectTBoxNodes() composes into a fully IRI-expanded @graph \u00e2\u20ac\u201d developer acknowledges this explicitly. (2) N3.js NodeNext named-import compatibility is uncertain; developer provides a fallback path. (3) UTF-8 BOM on src/tbox/project-tbox.ttl (applier default) will be accepted by N3.js for AC1/AC2 but may affect AC3 golden-file byte equality when OED-313 closes \u00e2\u20ac\u201d no impact on current tests. (4) The developer recommends queuing semantic-sme review before the apply step for the .ttl file (verbatim SPEC content, so review is expected confirmatory). These are apply-chain operational decisions; none are grounds for denial or deferral of the ratification.",
        "referenced_evidence": [
          {
            "type": "upstream_task",
            "id": "urn:fnsr:task:087-recon-tbox-bundle",
