        "open_questions": [
          "MISSING_REALIST_ANCHOR vs LEGACY_REALIST_ANCHOR_PLACEHOLDER overlap: IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md section 1.3 AC explicitly says MISSING_REALIST_ANCHOR fires for [\"ecm:UnspecifiedSubjectMatter\"] (implemented as proposed). But section 1.9 AC says migrate(v0.3Fixture, \"0.4\") + validate() produces zero hard errors (only LEGACY_REALIST_ANCHOR_PLACEHOLDER). If MISSING_REALIST_ANCHOR is a hard error that fires for the placeholder, task 1.9 cannot satisfy its AC without either (a) the validator distinguishing migration context (requires an extra parameter, changing the validate() signature), or (b) the migration path stripping ecm:UnspecifiedSubjectMatter and emitting LEGACY_REALIST_ANCHOR_PLACEHOLDER instead of MISSING_REALIST_ANCHOR from the validate() call. This is a deliberation-worthy ambiguity -- operator should resolve before task 1.9 dispatch.",
          "Module location for validate() is resolved as src/validate/ per task inputs scope_constraints (which named src/validate/ explicitly). No ADR proposed since this was settled by the task. If operator intended src/kernel/validate.ts instead, that changes the purity checker scope (the checker only scans src/kernel/ files -- adding validate.ts there subjects it to the FORBIDDEN_PATTERNS check, which would flag the regex literal as a false-positive-free path but would also prevent any future imports from src/tbox/).",
