    {
      "@id": "urn:fnsr:task:100-rat-semantic-projection",
      "agent": "architect",
      "status": "done",
      "attempts": 1,
      "outputs": {
        "ruling": "ratified",
        "editorial_verdict": "substantive",
        "editorial_verdict_reason": "The proposed change introduces new source code (`src/projection/index.ts`) and a new test file (`tests/semantic-projection.test.ts`), implementing a previously-absent algorithm and its acceptance-criteria test suite \u00e2\u20ac\u201d wholly outside the editorial-correction scope of typo fixes, formatting, or terminology tightening.",
        "rationale": "Reconnaissance is present in UPSTREAM (`urn:fnsr:task:098-recon-semantic-projection`), satisfying the Spec 03 prerequisite for substantive changes. The proposal was evaluated across all six review-focus dimensions:\n\n**1. Reconciliation with reconnaissance findings.** All 18 reconnaissance findings are addressed or acknowledged. F1 (no projectSemantic) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 C1 creates it. F2 (dependencies implemented) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 correctly imported. F3/F4 (ecm:name tension) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 strict \u00c2\u00a76.1 allowlist adopted; deviation from \u00c2\u00a76.2 prose documented in code comment and OQ1. F5 (rdfs:label discard on relations) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 `relationToTriple()` outputs only ecm:subjectIri/ecm:predicateIri/ecm:objectIri; rdfs:label is never included. F6 (fast-check absent) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 Mulberry32 PRNG hand-roll satisfies \u00e2\u2030\u00a550-sample AC3 without a new devDep. F7 (no test file) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 C2 creates it. F8 (rdfs:domain/range IRI gap) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 documented as OQ3, no breaking behavior. F9 (TBox @graph ambiguity) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 TBox-in-@graph assumption followed, consistent with IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN \u00c2\u00a71.5. F10 (auto-discovery) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 .test.ts compiles to .test.js and will be auto-discovered. F11 (DUPLICATE_TRIPLE validator deferred) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 not a projectSemantic blocker. F12 (type allowlist) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 9-entry Set correctly covers both ecm:Project and iao:OntologyDesignPattern as separate entries (project root carries both). F13/F16 (canvas-layout-invariance) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 AC3 verified via byte-comparison of canonical output, which is strictly stronger than the \u00c2\u00a76.4 semantic-equivalence definition. F17 (NAMED_ARRAY_KEYS private) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 not needed; implementation pre-sorts @graph before calling serializeVmp, bypassing the issue. F18 (test infrastructure gap) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 hand-rolled runner followed. F14/F15 \u00e2\u2020\u2019 not directly relevant.\n\n**2. SPEC \u00c2\u00a76.3 + \u00c2\u00a78.2 + \u00c2\u00a78.3 conformance.** All six \u00c2\u00a76.3 steps are implemented in order: (1) project document as input, (2) type-allowlist filter via `hasSemanticType()`, (3) predicate-allowlist filter via `applyPredicateFilter()`, (4) relation rewrite via `relationToTriple()` with Set-based dedup per \u00c2\u00a78.2, (5) TBox node insertion into @graph, (6) `serializeVmp()` call. \u00c2\u00a78.3's specific discard of relation id, timestamps, and rdfs:label is correctly implemented: `relationToTriple()` constructs a bare object from only the three IRI fields \u00e2\u20ac\u201d all other relation fields are structurally absent from the output.\n\n**3. All 5 ACs addressed.** AC1: @graph type-scan + raw string scan for canvas types. AC2: count of alice-knows-bob triples asserted === 1. AC3: 50-sample seeded loop (seed=0xDEADBEEF, Mulberry32). AC4: node with both iao:OntologyDesignPattern and ecm:Project in type[] found; iao:isAbout checked for presence and deepStrictEqual to input. AC5: string scan for ecm:specVersion, ecm:createdAt, ecm:updatedAt. All five are covered.\n\n**4. Property-based test.** Mulberry32 is a well-known pure-arithmetic PRNG; the test is deterministic per fixed seed and produces 50 structurally varied canvas-layout configurations. The seeded-loop pattern is appropriate for a hand-rolled property-based test without fast-check. The STABLE_ID idiom correctly isolates layout variance from identity variance.\n\n**5. Kernel purity and layer boundaries.** `src/projection/index.ts` imports only from `../kernel/canonicalize.js` and `../tbox/index.js`. No adapters/, composition/, I/O, Date.now(), Math.random(), or non-deterministic APIs appear anywhere in C1. The purity checker (`npm run test:purity`) targets `src/kernel/`; the new `src/projection/` module is correctly placed as a sibling to `src/tbox/` and `src/validate/` (established pattern for non-kernel domain modules that consume kernel primitives).\n\n**6. DevDep additions.** No new devDependencies are added; fast-check is not introduced. The gap-12 @types/* companion requirement is vacuously satisfied.\n\n**One advisory observation logged as banking (not a blocking concern):** The pre-sort of @graph before calling serializeVmp is correctly motivated (\"@graph\" is absent from NAMED_ARRAY_KEYS), but this creates an implicit coupling: if serializeVmp were ever extended to sort @graph, projectSemantic's pre-sort would become redundant rather than harmful (sort is idempotent for the stable comparator used). This is a low-risk coupling at current scope.\n\n**Open questions (OQ1\u00e2\u20ac\u201cOQ4) do not block ratification.** OQ1 (ecm:name) has a one-line fix path if OED resolves it; OQ2 (TBox ambiguity) follows the tracked IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN assumption; OQ3 (rdfs:domain/range expansion) is a known \u00c2\u00a77.5 deferral; OQ4 (idempotency scope) is correctly scoped to serializeVmp idempotency.\n\nRuling: ratified.",
        "referenced_evidence": [
          {
