    {
      "@id": "urn:fnsr:task:105-rat-emitters",
      "agent": "architect",
      "status": "done",
      "attempts": 1,
      "outputs": {
        "ruling": "ratified",
        "editorial_verdict": "substantive",
        "editorial_verdict_reason": "The proposal introduces four new source files (src/emit/turtle.ts, src/emit/n-triples.ts, src/emit/triple-narration.ts, tests/emitters.test.ts) implementing FR-C003, FR-C004, and FR-C008 with materially new runtime behavior; this is a functional addition, not a terminology or formatting correction.",
        "rationale": "Reconnaissance is present in UPSTREAM (urn:fnsr:task:103-recon-emitters) satisfying the refusal contract. The proposal is well-grounded in that reconnaissance and passes all review focus checks:\n\n**Reconnaissance reconciliation**: All 23 reconnaissance findings are addressed or properly deferred. F1 (no emit/ dir) resolved by the new files. F2 (projectSemantic covers FR-C005) acknowledged via Chain 2 thin-wrapper deferral. F3 (n3 devDep) surfaced as operator decision open_question 1 \u00e2\u20ac\u201d not silently ignored. F5/F18 (OED-301, OED-306, OED-313 gates) correctly reflected in AC stub pass entries. F6 (Mermaid/Markdown use raw project doc) correctly implemented in triple-narration.ts which reads from ecm:instances/ecm:relations directly. F11\u00e2\u20ac\u201cF12 (graphToQuads shape, TBox ambiguity) correctly handled: nodeToQuads converts @graph nodes including bare triples and LiteralAssertions; TBOX_IDS skip prevents re-serialization of TBox nodes already covered by the prepend. F16 (N3 Writer synchronous) relied upon correctly via the writer.end callback pattern already established in tbox-bundle.test.ts. F17 (idempotency requires stable @graph ordering) is satisfied because projectSemantic() pre-sorts allNamedNodes by id and bareTriples by composite key before returning; verified in AC6 tests.\n\n**SPEC \u00c2\u00a76.3 conformance**: Turtle emitter correctly follows the \u00c2\u00a76.3 algorithm: calls projectSemantic() for steps 1\u00e2\u20ac\u201c4 and 6; prepends getProjectTBoxTurtle() for step 5. N-Triples emitter re-serializes the Turtle TBox via N3.js Parser\u00e2\u2020\u2019Writer(format:N-Triples) per IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN \u00c2\u00a71.5 (recon F19 confirmed this is the right approach). The \u00c2\u00a76.3 note that Mermaid/Markdown use the simpler raw-document view is correctly honored: triple-narration.ts operates on the raw project document, not projectSemantic() output.\n\n**SPEC \u00c2\u00a77.1 + \u00c2\u00a75.8 conformance**: ecm:classIris \u00e2\u2020\u2019 rdf:type expansion is implemented in nodeToQuads() and verified by the Turtle content test (hasTriple check for INST_A_IRI rdf:type TERM_IRI). The `type` discriminator field is also serialized as rdf:type triples \u00e2\u20ac\u201d this is the developer's open_question 2, surfaced for OED clarification. N3.js AC1/AC2 parse tests pass regardless; the open question is semantic, not syntactic.\n\n**SPEC \u00c2\u00a75.10 + \u00c2\u00a79.1 conformance**: makeLiteralTerm correctly applies language tags when lang is non-null and datatype is xsd:string or rdf:langString; falls through to typed literal for all other datatypes. LiteralAssertion test in Turtle content block verifies the round-trip. AC6 idempotency tested for all three Chain 1 emitters and narrateProject.\n\n**SPEC \u00c2\u00a717.6 conformance**: AC1 and AC2 parse Turtle and N-Triples output through N3.js Parser; any syntactic error throws and fails the test. This is the required build-time conformance gate.\n\n**FR-C003\u00e2\u20ac\u201cFR-C008 scope coverage**: FR-C003 (emitTurtle) and FR-C004 (emitNTriples) fully implemented. FR-C008 (narrateTriple + narrateProject) fully implemented with template example from SPEC \u00c2\u00a718.1 verified by strictEqual. FR-C005 explicitly deferred to Chain 2 with tests_recommended entry. FR-C006 and FR-C007 explicitly deferred to Chain 3; AC4/AC5 are stubbed as passing stubs (acceptable per Phase 1 exit gate #12 which requires the structural Mermaid test to *pass*, not merely exist \u00e2\u20ac\u201d Chain 3 must deliver the actual test). This scope split is documented and appropriate.\n\n**Mermaid stub + OED-301**: No Mermaid emitter or truncation policy is proposed. AC4 is a named stub ('emitMermaid added in Chain 3'). OED-301 blocking golden files only is correctly stated. Phase 1 exit gate #12 confirms structural Mermaid test must pass, creating a firm dependency on Chain 3 before Phase 1 exit.\n\n**Golden-file ACs deferred per OED-306 + OED-313**: AC3 is explicitly stubbed with commentary referencing both OEDs. Correct.\n\n**Kernel purity / layer boundaries**: turtle.ts, n-triples.ts, and triple-narration.ts each declare the layer boundary constraint in their file headers and imports confirm no src/adapters/ or src/composition/ references. src/emit/ sits above src/projection/ and src/tbox/ in the dependency graph (which in turn depend on src/kernel/), preserving the Layer 0 isolation. The purity checker (npm run test:purity) tests src/kernel/ isolation and will not be triggered by src/emit/ imports.\n\n**One ratifiable concern not blocking**: The n3 devDep\u00e2\u2020\u2019dep reclassification is required before production deployment of the emitters. This is operator-gated, not implementation-gated. Phase 1 testing via npm test has devDependencies available and is unaffected. The developer correctly refuses to change package.json unilaterally given the CLAUDE.md \u00c2\u00a76 constraint.",
