        "summary": "Four TypeScript type errors exist in `src/emit/turtle.ts` and `src/emit/n-triples.ts`, arising from two structurally independent root causes. Root Cause A (errors at turtle.ts:131 and turtle.ts:154): the module-private helper `termForIri` has an inferred return type of `NamedNode<string> | BlankNode`, and both call sites pass `termForIri(p)` in the predicate position of `DataFactory.quad`. Per `@types/n3` (index.d.ts:113\u00e2\u20ac\u201c115) and `@rdfjs/types` (data-model.d.ts:147), the predicate argument must satisfy `RDF.Quad_Predicate = NamedNode | Variable`; `BlankNode` is absent from that union in both the n3 and RDF-js definitions. Root Cause B (errors at turtle.ts:259 and n-triples.ts:49): the return-type annotations `ReturnType<typeof makeQuad>[]` used on `nodeToQuads`, `graphToQuads`, and their local `result`/`quads` variables resolve \u00e2\u20ac\u201d in TypeScript 5.7's last-overload ReturnType inference \u00e2\u20ac\u201d to `n3.BaseQuad[]` rather than `n3.Quad[]`, because the last overload of `DataFactoryInterface.quad` is a generic returning `Q_Out extends BaseQuad`; TypeScript infers the constraint (`BaseQuad`), not the default (`Quad`). `n3.BaseQuad` is not assignable to `RDF.Quad` because its `subject` and `predicate` properties are typed as the wide `n3.Term` union (which includes `Literal` and `DefaultGraph`), which is not a subtype of `RDF.Quad_Subject` or `RDF.Quad_Predicate`. The `Writer.addQuads(quads: RDF.Quad[])` calls at lines 259 and 49 therefore fail. The analogous `tboxWriter.addQuads(tboxQuads)` call at n-triples.ts:38 is NOT an error because `tboxQuads` derives from `Parser<Quad>.parse()` and carries the concrete `n3.Quad[]` type, which does implement `RDF.Quad`. No additional predicate-position violations exist at the other five `makeQuad` call sites in turtle.ts (all use `namedNode(...)` directly). `triple-narration.ts` imports no n3 types and is unaffected.",
