        "open_questions": [
          "SPEC \u00c2\u00a79.3 says UUIDv5 is derived from 'the seed and the operation context' without specifying the UUIDv5 namespace UUID (RFC 4122 \u00c2\u00a74.3 requires a namespace UUID as part of the SHA-1 input). Which namespace UUID should be used \u00e2\u20ac\u201d one of the predefined RFC 4122 namespaces (DNS, URL, OID, X500), or a project-defined custom namespace IRI?",
          "What is the canonical definition of 'operation context' for UUIDv5 mode? Is it the entity label, a sequence counter, the baseIri + classSlug + labelSlug combination, or some other string derived from the creation operation?",
          "The src/validate/index.ts stub comment attributes wiring of id/ecm:createdAt to task 1.6, but developer task 114 scope_constraints prohibit modifying src/validate/*. Is the validate-report wiring deferred to a separate follow-up task (not yet queued), or is the scope_constraint intended to be relaxed for that specific wiring?",
