    {
      "@id": "urn:fnsr:task:115-rat-iri-generation",
      "agent": "architect",
      "status": "done",
      "attempts": 1,
      "outputs": {
        "ruling": "ratified",
        "editorial_verdict": "substantive",
        "editorial_verdict_reason": "The proposed change creates two new source modules (src/iri/index.ts, tests/iri-generation.test.ts), implements RFC 4122 \u00c2\u00a74.3 UUIDv5 logic and UUIDv4 generation, exports a typed public API (IriPolicy, IriContext, generateIri), and adds tests covering three SPEC-mandated acceptance criteria \u00e2\u20ac\u201d all of which constitute new behavioral and structural content, not editorial correction.",
        "rationale": "Reconnaissance is present in UPSTREAM (task 113-recon-iri-generation). All 22 recon findings are reconciled in the developer proposal. The ratification is granted on the following grounds:\n\n1. SPEC \u00c2\u00a79.2 CONFORMANCE: UUIDv4 non-determinism is acknowledged by SPEC as 'non-deterministic only until persisted.' The proposal correctly confines crypto.randomUUID() to the ecm:uuid-urn path inside src/iri/ (outside src/kernel/), and the inline comment in the proposed code explicitly cites SPEC \u00c2\u00a79.2. The manualUuidV4() Math.random() fallback is acceptable for the same reason: src/iri/ is outside the kernel purity checker's enforcement scope (confirmed: scripts/ensure-kernel-purity.ts line 22 scans dist-tests/src/kernel/ only, per recon F7). No kernel purity regression occurs.\n\n2. SPEC \u00c2\u00a79.3 CONFORMANCE: The ecm:deterministic code path is a pure function \u00e2\u20ac\u201d no Date.now(), no Math.random(), no process.env. seed and entityContext are explicit parameters. The UUIDv5 implementation uses createHash('sha1') from node:crypto (synchronous; not Web Crypto API), which is compatible with the pure-function constraint for the deterministic path.\n\n3. RFC 4122 \u00c2\u00a74.3 IMPLEMENTATION CORRECTNESS: (a) UUID_V5_NAMESPACE is the RFC 4122 URL namespace (6ba7b811-9dad-11d1-80b4-00c04fd430c8) encoded as 16 bytes in network byte order (big-endian) \u00e2\u20ac\u201d verified byte-for-byte correct. (b) SHA-1 input is correctly constructed: namespace buffer followed by name UTF-8 bytes. (c) Version bits: hash[6] = (hash[6] & 0x0f) | 0x50 \u00e2\u20ac\u201d sets high nibble to 0101 (version 5). (d) Variant bits: hash[8] = (hash[8] & 0x3f) | 0x80 \u00e2\u20ac\u201d sets two high bits to 10xx (RFC 4122 IETF variant). (e) Hex slice 8-4-4-4-12 over first 32 chars of 40-char SHA-1 hex output uses the first 16 bytes of the 20-byte digest, which is correct per RFC 4122 \u00c2\u00a74.3.\n\n4. AC1 (regex): ecm:uuid-urn mode returns urn:uuid: + crypto.randomUUID(). Node 22's crypto.randomUUID() produces lowercase hex UUIDv4 without prefix; the template literal adds urn:uuid:. The AC1 regex (^urn:uuid:[0-9a-f]{8}-[0-9a-f]{4}-4[0-9a-f]{3}-[89ab][0-9a-f]{3}-[0-9a-f]{12}$) is satisfied. The manualUuidV4 fallback sets version nibble to 0x4X (hex '4') and variant nibble to 0x8X\u00e2\u20ac\u201c0xBX (hex [89ab]) \u00e2\u20ac\u201d both correct. Three-call robustness check included.\n\n5. AC2 (deterministic reproducibility): ecm:deterministic invokes generateUuidV5('${seed}|${entityContext}') \u00e2\u20ac\u201d a pure SHA-1 hash, so identical inputs always produce identical output. Two-call and five-call checks both included.\n\n6. AC3 (different contexts produce different IRIs): UUIDv5 with different name strings (CTX_A vs CTX_B, SEED_A vs SEED_B) produce different SHA-1 hashes with overwhelming probability; notStrictEqual assertions verify this. Both different-entityContext and different-seed sub-cases covered.\n\n7. AC4 DEFERRAL: Properly deferred per OED-313 with a stub pass following the existing pattern in tests/structural-validator.test.ts.\n\n8. LAYER BOUNDARIES: src/iri/index.ts imports only from node:crypto. No imports from src/adapters/ or src/composition/. MUST NOT constraint (CLAUDE.md \u00c2\u00a76) satisfied.\n\n9. DEVDEP ADDITIONS: No new npm packages added. node:crypto is a Node stdlib module; crypto.randomUUID() and createHash() are fully typed by the existing @types/node@^22.0.0 devDep (confirmed by recon F5, F16). ADR-001 zero-runtime-dependency constraint (recon F6) is preserved.\n\n10. TEST FILE STRUCTURE: Hand-rolled runner pattern (node:assert, pass/fail counter, process.exit(1)) matches all existing test files in tests/ (recon F15). Import path ../src/iri/index.js matches tsconfig.test.json rootDir/outDir structure (dist-tests/ compilation root; relative import consistent with existing tests/emitters.test.ts, tests/semantic-projection.test.ts, etc.).\n\n11. OPEN QUESTIONS \u00e2\u20ac\u201d NOT BLOCKING: (a) UUIDv5 namespace not specified in SPEC \u00c2\u00a79.3 (recon F9, dev open_question 1): developer uses RFC 4122 URL namespace as documented pragmatic default, with inline NOTE flagging for ADR ratification before AC4 is un-deferred. This is acceptable because AC4 (the AC that would require byte-identical golden output) is itself deferred per OED-313, so the namespace lock is not required to close AC1\u00e2\u20ac\u201cAC3. (b) src/validate/* stub wiring gap (recon F14, dev open_question 4): developer correctly identifies that scope_constraints prohibit src/validate/* modification; the gap is explicitly documented and deferred to a follow-up task. No hiding of scope limitation.\n\n12. SPEC \u00c2\u00a75.5 PATTERN FIELDS: The \u00c2\u00a75.5 ecm:pattern ({baseIri}{classSlug}_{labelSlug}_{uuid}) expansion fields are not addressed by IMPL \u00c2\u00a71.6 ACs. Recon F12 correctly characterized this as an inference that AC1 is scoped to UUID generation only (urn:uuid: strings), with pattern-expansion deferred to a later task. No blocking issue.\n\n13. SPEC \u00c2\u00a713.9 PERSISTED-IRI STABILITY: Recon F22 correctly identified this as a transform-layer constraint, not a generateIri constraint. The generateIri function is stateless by design; persisted-IRI stability is enforced by the project document handling layer, not the IRI generation function itself.",
        "referenced_evidence": [
