        "summary": "Task 117 (test-runner) recorded exactly 6 TypeScript compilation errors from tsc build:tests; tests did not execute. Five errors are clustered in src/iri/index.ts lines 71-79 within the manualUuidV4() fallback function, and one error is in tests/iri-generation.test.ts line 99. The root cause in both locations is the same: Array.from<T>(iterable, mapfn) called with 1 explicit type argument alongside a mapfn second argument. TypeScript 5.9.3's overload resolution for Array.from exposes four overloads (two 1-type-param, two 2-type-param); providing a single explicit type argument restricts overload candidates to the 1-type-param forms, which accept exactly 1 argument \u00e2\u20ac\u201d making the mapfn a superfluous second argument (TS2554 at src/iri/index.ts:71,52 and tests/iri-generation.test.ts:99,50). After the TS2554, TypeScript error-recovery infers the element type of bytes as unknown rather than number, cascading to TS2571 at lines 75 and 77 (bytes[6] and bytes[8] on the RHS of bit-manipulation assignments) and TS18046 at line 79 col 29 and 51 (both uses of b in the .map() callback). All errors are confined to two files added in task 1.6 (src/iri/index.ts and tests/iri-generation.test.ts); no other test or source file in the codebase uses this Array.from pattern. The generateUuidV5 function and the nodeRandomUUID call site in src/iri/index.ts are free of type errors per the @types/node 22.19.11 declarations.",
