      "outputs": {
        "ruling": "ratified",
        "editorial_verdict": "substantive",
        "editorial_verdict_reason": "The proposal adds two entirely new source files\u00e2\u20ac\u201dsrc/refactor/index.ts (a new kernel-adjacent module with a new exported function) and tests/iri-refactor.test.ts (a new test suite)\u00e2\u20ac\u201dimplementing new behavioral capability; this is a code-and-behavior addition, not a textual or formatting correction.",
        "rationale": "Reconnaissance is present in UPSTREAM (urn:fnsr:task:123-recon-iri-refactor). All 15 recon findings are correctly addressed by the proposed change. No blocking structural issue was found. The detailed evaluation follows.\n\n**Reconciliation with reconnaissance.** F1/F2 (four target field types; LiteralAssertion carries subjectIri+predicateIri but NOT objectIri): \u00e2\u0153\u2026 Implementation correctly updates ecm:classIris on instances, ecm:predicateIri and ecm:subjectIri on both relations and literals, ecm:objectIri on relations only. F3/F15 (ecm:snapshots must not be touched at any depth): \u00e2\u0153\u2026 The spread `{...project, \"ecm:instances\": ..., \"ecm:relations\": ..., \"ecm:literalAssertions\": ...}` carries ecm:snapshots through untouched\u00e2\u20ac\u201dthe field is never listed in the overwrite set and the implementation contains no traversal into it. F4 (RefactorResult shape): \u00e2\u0153\u2026 Exactly matches { project, oldIri, newIri, referenceCount, affectedEntityTypes, collision? }. F5 (no src/refactor/ exists yet): \u00e2\u0153\u2026 New module is correctly placed at src/refactor/index.ts. F6/F7/F8 (Mulberry32 PRNG, no fast-check): \u00e2\u0153\u2026 Identical Mulberry32 implementation; no package.json change; fast-check discrepancy against IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN \u00c2\u00a71.12 properly surfaced as open question. F9 (entity-id scope gap): \u00e2\u0153\u2026 Implementation follows the sub-task enumeration exactly (four reference field types only); gap documented prominently in both the module header and test comments; disjoint-prefix fixture design (urn:test:ref: vs urn:test:eid:) makes the scope boundary structurally explicit. F10 (collision scan via entity id fields): \u00e2\u0153\u2026 collectSemanticEntityIds scans ecm:terms and ecm:instances. F11 (reversibility + idempotency invariants): \u00e2\u0153\u2026 Both implemented at \u00e2\u2030\u00a550 samples. F12/F13 (auto-discovery; serializeVmp for canonical comparison): \u00e2\u0153\u2026 test follows *.test.ts pattern; reversibility uses serializeVmp from src/kernel/canonicalize.js. F14 (collision = abort-and-report only; no merge path): \u00e2\u0153\u2026 Out-of-scope merge path not implemented; properly documented.\n\n**SPEC \u00c2\u00a713.1\u00e2\u20ac\u201c13.9 conformance.** \u00c2\u00a713.1 (identity principle): \u00e2\u0153\u2026 operation is explicit refactor. \u00c2\u00a713.2 (ecm:classIris + ecm:predicateIri cascade): \u00e2\u0153\u2026. \u00c2\u00a713.3 (imported term immutability): out of scope at this layer\u00e2\u20ac\u201dthe function operates on raw project documents; UI/adapter layer enforces import immutability. \u00c2\u00a713.4 (ecm:subjectIri + ecm:objectIri cascade): \u00e2\u0153\u2026. \u00c2\u00a713.5 (collision detect before apply): \u00e2\u0153\u2026. \u00c2\u00a713.6 (project-created replacing imported): out of scope (remap operation). \u00c2\u00a713.7 (snapshots not modified): \u00e2\u0153\u2026\u00e2\u20ac\u201dsee spread analysis above. \u00c2\u00a713.8 (UI refactor-vs-create-new): out of scope. \u00c2\u00a713.9 (deterministic IRI generation): out of scope.\n\n**FR-C010 and SPEC \u00c2\u00a721.1.** FR-C010 (cascade update with collision detection): \u00e2\u0153\u2026. SPEC \u00c2\u00a721.1 reversibility invariant: the invariant is stated universally but the IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN \u00c2\u00a71.7 sub-tasks enumerate only the four reference field types\u00e2\u20ac\u201dentity id fields are out of scope. The implementation satisfies the invariant conditionally (when oldIri is not an entity id). The gap is documented and a follow-up chain must adjudicate F9 before entity-id updating is added. The current proposal correctly implements the IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN \u00c2\u00a71.7 scope.\n\n**All 5 ACs covered.** AC1: full-document traversal with absence assertions on all four field types; exact referenceCount assertions (alpha=3, delta=2) against known fixture values; affectedEntityTypes deep-equality. AC2: bytewise identity enforced via same-object-reference check (result.project === BASE_PROJECT); referenceCount=0 and affectedEntityTypes=[] assertions; two sub-cases (ecm:terms id and ecm:instances id collision). AC3: 50 samples, seed 0xcafebabe, serializeVmp canonical comparison; disjoint-prefix design documented; scope note in test comments. AC4: 50 samples, seed 0xbeefdead; pool includes reference-field IRIs, entity ids, and absent IRIs. AC5: JSON.stringify comparison on ecm:snapshots across all three result paths (success, collision, no-op).\n\n**Kernel purity / layer boundaries.** src/refactor/index.ts is outside src/kernel/\u00e2\u20ac\u201dthe purity checker does not apply. No imports from src/adapters/ or src/composition/. No Date.now(), Math.random(), process.env, fetch, or any non-deterministic API. Import paths in the test use .js extension consistent with the TypeScript-to-ESM compilation pattern observed in existing tests (vmp-serializer.test.ts, semantic-projection.test.ts).\n\n**Open questions properly scoped.** All four open questions from the developer task are properly scoped and do not block this ratification: F9 entity-id scope (architect adjudication needed before follow-up chain); F14 collision scan scope (ecm:terms + ecm:instances is appropriate for MVP); F8 fast-check discrepancy (stale \u00c2\u00a71.12 language; hand-rolled is correct per CLAUDE.md \u00c2\u00a76 devDependencies rule); fixture realism contingent on F9 resolution.\n\n**No blocking issues.** The proposed change is internally consistent, conforms to IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN \u00c2\u00a71.7 ACs, correctly reconciles with all recon findings, respects layer boundaries, and does not introduce non-deterministic APIs. Operator may proceed to Pass 2b (applier).",
