        "bankings": [
          {
            "id": "B1",
            "category": "pattern-observation",
            "content": "The spread-with-explicit-overrides pattern ({...project, \"ecm:instances\": ..., \"ecm:relations\": ..., \"ecm:literalAssertions\": ...}) preserves ecm:snapshots bytewise-identity by construction: the field is carried through the spread without ever appearing in the override set or being traversed. This makes AC5 compliance implicit in the data-assembly structure rather than requiring an explicit guard or conditional. The pattern is worth canonicalizing in the PLAYBOOK for future cascade-update functions that must preserve non-target top-level arrays."
          },
          {
            "id": "B2",
            "category": "pattern-observation",
            "content": "Disjoint IRI prefix pool design for property-based test fixtures: using distinct urn: sub-namespaces (urn:test:ref: for reference-field values, urn:test:eid: for entity id fields) isolates two behavioral dimensions of a function\u00e2\u20ac\u201dcascade behavior vs. entity identity\u00e2\u20ac\u201denabling the reversibility invariant to be tested in isolation against a scoped implementation. The disjoint-prefix boundary becomes a self-documenting scope marker: when F9 is resolved (entity-id updates added), the test fixtures will need updating, and the delta will be structurally visible."
          },
          {
            "id": "B3",
            "category": "methodology-refinement-candidate",
            "content": "The IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN \u00c2\u00a71.12 references fast-check by name for four property-based invariants while the established codebase practice (adopted starting at task 1.4 semantic-projection) uses hand-rolled Mulberry32 with explicit Human Orchestrator approval required for new devDependencies per CLAUDE.md \u00c2\u00a76. The reconnaissance \u00e2\u2020\u2019 developer chain correctly surfaced this discrepancy and enforced the hand-rolled pattern without requiring operator intervention. This is a candidate refinement: \u00c2\u00a71.12 language should be updated in a future doc-pass to replace 'fast-check' references with 'hand-rolled Mulberry32 PRNG (or Human-Orchestrator-approved equivalent)' to prevent the same discrepancy from re-emerging in future tasks."
          }
        ]
