      "outputs": {
        "ruling": "ratified",
        "editorial_verdict": "substantive",
        "editorial_verdict_reason": "The proposed change adds two new production source files (src/manifest/index.ts, tests/manifest-entries.test.ts) implementing new functionality \u00e2\u20ac\u201d the generateManifestEntries function and its test suite \u00e2\u20ac\u201d not a formatting fix, terminology tightening, or citation update.",
        "rationale": "Reconnaissance is present in UPSTREAM (urn:fnsr:task:128-recon-manifest-entries, 18 findings). The developer's proposal addresses all recon findings and satisfies all four ratification criteria in the review_focus:\n\n**Reconciliation with recon**: All 18 findings accounted for. F1 (7 Required fields) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 implemented. F2/F3 (three-way count mismatch: SPEC=7, sub-tasks=8, AC='six') \u00e2\u2020\u2019 proposal implements 8 fields, correctly resolves toward the most inclusive enumeration consistent with multiple corroborating evidence points (\u00c2\u00a75.15 JSON example, \u00c2\u00a76.1 semantic predicate allowlist, \u00c2\u00a719 manifest description), and flags AC1's 'six' as a probable typo \u00e2\u20ac\u201d operator should issue an editorial correction to IMPL plan \u00c2\u00a71.8 AC1. F4 (MIME types) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 format passed from caller, correct deferral. F5 (sha256- prefix, UTF-8 byteLength) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 implemented per spec. F6 (no existing manifest module) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 proposal creates new files only. F7/F8 (node:crypto already in use, @types/node ^22.0.0 devDependency) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 no new dependencies; same API family. F9 (src/manifest/ outside src/kernel/, purity checker scope) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 verified via scripts/ensure-kernel-purity.ts:22. F10 (hand-rolled test pattern) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 test follows iri-generation.test.ts shape exactly. F11 (task 1.8 scope = data structure only) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 no manifest.jsonld document generation included. F12 (byteLength absent from Turtle example but in \u00c2\u00a76.1 allowlist) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 noted, implementation correct. F13 (generatedAt xsd:dateTime vs plain string) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 out of scope for task 1.8 data structure; deferred to emitter layer. F14/F15/F17/F18 \u00e2\u2020\u2019 all handled correctly in proposal.\n\n**SPEC \u00c2\u00a75.15 + \u00c2\u00a719 conformance**: SerializationEntry interface declares all 7 SPEC \u00c2\u00a75.15 Required fields (id, type, ecm:format, ecm:filename, ecm:contentHash, ecm:generatedAt, ecm:isSerializationOf) plus ecm:byteLength. type is correctly literals-typed as 'ecm:Serialization'. ecm:isSerializationOf references project root id per \u00c2\u00a75.15 line 662. \u00c2\u00a719 (line 1399) lists byteLength explicitly; its presence in the generated struct is correct. No \u00c2\u00a75.15 Required field is absent.\n\n**All 4 ACs covered**: AC1 (schema assertion) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 test asserts all 8 fields with correct shapes on each entry, including UUID format check and sha256- prefix check. AC2 (isSerializationOf equals project root id) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 tested with two-project variant and absent-project-id guard. AC3 (contentHash reference hash comparison) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 test independently computes SHA-256 of known string using createHash and compares; Buffer/string parity also tested. AC4 (byteLength = UTF-8 byte length) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 multi-byte 'caf\u00c3\u00a9' (5 UTF-8 bytes for 4 chars) tested explicitly; ASCII count and Buffer input also tested.\n\n**Crypto API / gap-13**: createHash('sha256').update(contentBuf).digest('hex') uses the typed string-returning overload (Hash.digest(encoding: BinaryEncoding): string from @types/node). This avoids the TS2571 pattern from task 1.5/1.6 recovery chains, where .digest() without an encoding argument returned Buffer and TypeScript inferred 'unknown' after error recovery. The proposal uses explicit `const digest: string = ...` type annotation to make the intent checkable at compile time. No new runtime dependencies; @types/node ^22.0.0 is already in devDependencies per package.json:33.\n\n**Kernel purity / layer boundaries**: src/manifest/ is outside src/kernel/; the purity checker (scripts/ensure-kernel-purity.ts:22) only scans src/kernel/. No imports from src/adapters/ or src/composition/. Import of generateIri from ../iri/index.js uses .js NodeNext extension per tsconfig.json module/moduleResolution:NodeNext, consistent with all existing cross-module imports (verified in tests/ and src/emit/turtle.ts). Test imports from ../src/manifest/index.js, consistent with the pattern across all other test files (determinism.test.ts, iri-generation.test.ts, emitters.test.ts, etc.).\n\n**generatedAt determinism**: The function never calls Date.now() internally; generatedAt is threaded from the caller (ArtifactInput.generatedAt). This correctly extends SPEC \u00c2\u00a79.3 determinism discipline to a module outside the kernel purity enforcement scope.\n\n**Scope boundary**: No existing files are modified. The proposal adds exactly two files. The full manifest.jsonld RDF document generation is correctly deferred to Phase 4 task 4.5 per IMPL plan \u00c2\u00a71.8 and \u00c2\u00a74.5.\n\nOne operator action recommended post-ratification: issue an editorial correction to IMPL plan \u00c2\u00a71.8 AC1 text to replace 'six' with '7 (or 8 including ecm:byteLength)' \u00e2\u20ac\u201d the current text is inconsistent with both SPEC \u00c2\u00a75.15 Required: line (7) and the sub-tasks enumeration (8).",
