        "bankings": [
          {
            "id": "B1",
            "category": "pattern-observation",
            "content": "Three-way field count mismatch resolution: when a SPEC Required: line (7 fields), a sub-tasks enumeration (8 fields), and an AC text ('six') all disagree, the correct architectural resolution is to implement the union consistent with multiple corroborating evidence points (\u00c2\u00a75.15 JSON example, \u00c2\u00a76.1 semantic predicate allowlist, \u00c2\u00a719 description, sub-tasks enumeration) and flag the AC text discrepancy for an editorial correction. The ratification pass is the right place to surface this resolution rather than veto a conformant implementation. The developer's transparent documentation of the mismatch (open_questions + in-code comments) is the correct discipline."
          },
          {
            "id": "B2",
            "category": "pattern-observation",
            "content": "SPEC \u00c2\u00a79.3 determinism discipline applied outside kernel purity scope: threading `generatedAt` from the caller (never calling Date.now() internally) in src/manifest/index.ts, a module outside src/kernel/ and therefore outside the kernel purity checker's enforcement scope, demonstrates that the \u00c2\u00a79.3 determinism discipline can and should be applied by convention in non-kernel modules even when the purity checker does not enforce it. This is the second instance of this pattern (src/iri/index.ts uses ecm:deterministic mode for the same reason). The convention is: non-kernel modules that interact with time must accept timestamps as explicit parameters; they must not source time internally."
          },
          {
            "id": "B3",
            "category": "discipline-correction",
            "content": "gap-13 TypeScript crypto type-safety canon: the correct pattern for node:crypto Hash.digest() in this codebase is .digest('hex') (returns string, typed as BinaryEncoding overload) rather than .digest() (returns Buffer, and under certain TypeScript error-recovery conditions was inferred as unknown, producing TS2571). The task 1.5 and 1.6 recovery chains were caused by the untyped form. The canonical form \u00e2\u20ac\u201d `const digest: string = createHash('sha256').update(buf).digest('hex')` \u00e2\u20ac\u201d uses an explicit type annotation to make the intent checkable at compile time and uses the string-returning overload to avoid Buffer type-narrowing requirements. This pattern should be applied consistently to all future node:crypto digest calls in this codebase."
          }
        ]
      },
