      "@id": "urn:fnsr:task:133-recon-legacy-migration",
      "agent": "reconnaissance",
      "status": "done",
      "attempts": 1,
      "outputs": {
        "findings": [
          {
            "id": "F1",
            "claim": "SPEC.md \u00c2\u00a710.3 defines the migrate() function signature as `migrate(projectDocument, targetVersion) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 { document, migrationReport }` where the migration report lists each field added, removed, or transformed; the function is the core layer's responsibility with a non-destructive disk contract.",
            "evidence": [
              {
                "file": "project/SPEC.md",
                "lines": "875-883",
                "excerpt": "migrate(projectDocument, targetVersion) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 { document, migrationReport }\nMigration is the responsibility of the receiving (newer) version. A v0.4 implementation must migrate v0.3 documents. The migration report lists each field added, removed, or transformed.\nMigration is non-destructive: the original document is preserved on disk under `project.jsonld.pre-migration.<sourceVersion>` unless the caller opts out."
              }
            ],
            "kind": "observation"
          },
          {
            "id": "F2",
            "claim": "SPEC.md \u00c2\u00a710.4 identifies v0.2 documents by three structural absences: missing `ecm:specVersion`, missing `ecm:literalAssertions`, and missing `rdfs:subClassOf`/`rdfs:subPropertyOf` on terms.",
            "evidence": [
              {
                "file": "project/SPEC.md",
                "lines": "887",
                "excerpt": "**v0.2 documents** (missing `ecm:specVersion`, missing `ecm:literalAssertions`, missing `rdfs:subClassOf` / `rdfs:subPropertyOf` on terms) are loaded as legacy v0.2 and migrated through v0.3 to v0.4 on load."
              }
            ],
            "kind": "observation"
          },
          {
            "id": "F3",
            "claim": "SPEC.md \u00c2\u00a710.4 defines exactly five v0.3\u00e2\u2020\u2019v0.4 migration transforms plus one info-finding emission: (1) update `ecm:specVersion` to `\"0.4\"`, (2) expand `@context` with `iao:`/`cco:` per \u00c2\u00a75.2, (3) update root `type` from `\"ecm:Project\"` to `[\"ecm:Project\", \"iao:OntologyDesignPattern\"]`, (4) initialize `iao:isAbout` to `[\"ecm:UnspecifiedSubjectMatter\"]`, (5) initialize `ecm:serializations` to `[]`, and (6) emit `LEGACY_REALIST_ANCHOR_PLACEHOLDER` info finding.",
            "evidence": [
              {
                "file": "project/SPEC.md",
                "lines": "891-898",
                "excerpt": "The v0.3 \u00e2\u2020\u2019 v0.4 migration:\n- updates `ecm:specVersion` to `\"0.4\"`;\n- expands the `@context` to include `iao:` and `cco:` prefixes per \u00c2\u00a75.2;\n- updates the project root's `type` from `\"ecm:Project\"` to `[\"ecm:Project\", \"iao:OntologyDesignPattern\"]`;\n- initializes `iao:isAbout` to `[\"ecm:UnspecifiedSubjectMatter\"]` (the placeholder);\n- emits a `LEGACY_REALIST_ANCHOR_PLACEHOLDER` info finding (\u00c2\u00a717.4);\n- initializes `ecm:serializations` to `[]`."
              }
            ],
            "kind": "observation"
          },
          {
            "id": "F4",
            "claim": "SPEC.md \u00c2\u00a710.4 specifies that the v0.2\u00e2\u2020\u2019v0.3 migration leg runs first, then the v0.3\u00e2\u2020\u2019v0.4 leg runs on top \u00e2\u20ac\u201d establishing a chained two-step migration path for v0.2 documents.",
            "evidence": [
