        "summary": "Phase 1 task 1.9 (Legacy Migration) is fully unimplemented: `src/migrate/` does not exist, no migration tests exist, and no test fixtures exist under `tests/fixtures/`. The SPEC and IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN together fully specify the task: a two-step chained migration function `migrate(doc, targetVersion) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 {document, migrationReport}` handling v0.2\u00e2\u2020\u2019v0.3 (add specVersion, literalAssertions, settings defaults, subclass/subproperty stubs) then v0.3\u00e2\u2020\u2019v0.4 (update specVersion, @context, type array, init iao:isAbout and ecm:serializations, emit LEGACY_REALIST_ANCHOR_PLACEHOLDER info finding). The forward-track open question ft-097-test-validator-3 \u00e2\u20ac\u201d whether MISSING_REALIST_ANCHOR fires alongside LEGACY_REALIST_ANCHOR_PLACEHOLDER after migration \u00e2\u20ac\u201d is resolved by two canonical sources: SPEC \u00c2\u00a75.4.1 uses exclusive \"or\" language making the two findings mutually exclusive by provenance, and IMPL PLAN \u00c2\u00a71.9 AC2 directly requires zero hard errors when migrate()+validate() are chained. This establishes that MISSING_REALIST_ANCHOR must be suppressed in legacy-migrated documents, requiring a modification to `src/validate/index.ts` to accept migration provenance context. The existing VMP_CONTEXT in `src/kernel/canonicalize.ts` already contains the v0.4 iao:/cco: prefixes and is reusable by migrate(). An open tension exists in the severity taxonomy: \u00c2\u00a717.1 declares info findings \"informational only\" but LEGACY_REALIST_ANCHOR_PLACEHOLDER (info) blocks export per \u00c2\u00a717.4 \u00e2\u20ac\u201d this is unresolved in DECISIONS.md (ADR-001 through ADR-006 are present; none addresses it), and the implementation must navigate it without SPEC ambiguity resolution. FR-C013 covers only v0.2\u00e2\u2020\u2019v0.3; no FR-C identifier covers v0.3\u00e2\u2020\u2019v0.4 (a gap confirmed by prior spec-reviewer finding F3 in state.jsonld). Golden-file AC4 for the test fixture is deferred pending OED-306.",
