          "Recon open question F15 (LEGACY_REALIST_ANCHOR_PLACEHOLDER is section 17.1 'info' yet blocks export per section 17.4): this implementation does NOT add export-blocking logic \u00e2\u20ac\u201d that belongs in the CLI/adapter layer (task 1.11+). The validate() finding is emitted as ecm:info severity exactly as declared in codes.ts. The tension between section 17.1 'info = informational only' and section 17.4 'does not block save but does block export' is unresolved in DECISIONS.md (ADR-001 through ADR-006 cover other topics). Flagged for operator awareness; no ADR exists to cite here.",
          "Recon open question: snapshot migration (SPEC section 10.5) is cited in IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md section 1.9 SPEC refs but has no AC1-AC5 test case. This proposal scopes to AC1-AC5 only. Snapshot migration is treated as deferred.",
          "The targetVersion guard (unsupported target returns INVALID_SPEC_VERSION) is a defensive addition not explicitly in the ACs. If the operator prefers the function silently no-op on unknown targets, the guard in migrate() should be removed and targetVersion marked with a leading underscore."
        ],
        "summary": "Three new/modified files. C1 creates src/migrate/index.ts implementing migrate(doc, targetVersion='0.4'): MigrateResult with a chained v0.2->v0.3->v0.4 migration path, INVALID_SPEC_VERSION rejection for forward-version inputs, and the ft-097-test-validator-3 Option A marker (ecm:_legacyAnchorPlaceholder: true set during the v0.3->v0.4 leg). C2-C5 make four targeted patches to src/validate/index.ts: add LEGACY_REALIST_ANCHOR_PLACEHOLDER to the import, insert a makeInfo() helper, replace the MISSING_REALIST_ANCHOR check block with a two-branch check that suppresses the hard error and emits the info finding when the marker is present, and update the TODO comment. C6 creates tests/legacy-migration.test.ts covering AC1 (v0.2->v0.4 specVersion and iao:isAbout), AC2 (v0.3->v0.4 + validate() yields zero errors and exactly one LEGACY_REALIST_ANCHOR_PLACEHOLDER info finding \u00e2\u20ac\u201d ft-097 resolved), AC3 (migration report enumerates all 5 changed fields), AC4 (deferred per OED-306), and AC5 (v0.5 input returns INVALID_SPEC_VERSION error with null document/report). ft-097-test-validator-3 is explicitly resolved via Option A: SPEC section 5.4.1's exclusive 'or' language and IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md section 1.9 AC2 together establish mutual exclusivity by provenance; no new ADR is needed since the canonical sources are unambiguous.",
