          "RESOLUTION OF ft-097-test-validator-3: when migration sets iao:isAbout to UnspecifiedSubjectMatter, the resulting validate() should NOT also fire MISSING_REALIST_ANCHOR (per AC2 which says ONLY LEGACY_REALIST_ANCHOR_PLACEHOLDER info finding present). Two ways to achieve this: (A) Migration adds a marker field (e.g., ecm:_legacyAnchorPlaceholder: true) and MISSING_REALIST_ANCHOR check suppresses when marker present; OR (B) The validator checks 'iao:isAbout contains UnspecifiedSubjectMatter' AND 'doc was loaded via migration' (migration sets a flag the validator reads). Choose Option A or B per recon findings; cleaner is probably A (marker field that doesn't bleed into export).",
