        "ruling": "ratified",
        "editorial_verdict": "substantive",
        "editorial_verdict_reason": "The proposed change creates a new module (src/migrate/index.ts), modifies validate() logic in src/validate/index.ts to suppress a hard error under a migration-provenance condition, and adds a new test file \u00e2\u20ac\u201d these are behaviorally new capabilities that alter the system's functional surface, not formatting or terminology corrections.",
        "rationale": "Reconnaissance is present in UPSTREAM (urn:fnsr:task:133-recon-legacy-migration) with 23 findings spanning all six review focus areas. The proposed change passes on all load-bearing dimensions:\n\n**ft-097-test-validator-3 resolution (Option A):** The developer chose the in-document marker approach (ecm:_legacyAnchorPlaceholder: true set during the v0.3\u00e2\u2020\u2019v0.4 leg) to discriminate LEGACY_REALIST_ANCHOR_PLACEHOLDER from MISSING_REALIST_ANCHOR in validate(). This is grounded in two canonical sources: SPEC \u00c2\u00a75.4.1 uses exclusive-disjunction language ('emits MISSING_REALIST_ANCHOR (an error) or LEGACY_REALIST_ANCHOR_PLACEHOLDER (info, after v0.3 migration)'), and IMPL PLAN \u00c2\u00a71.9 AC2 directly requires 'zero hard errors (only LEGACY_REALIST_ANCHOR_PLACEHOLDER info finding)' when migrate()+validate() are chained. No ADR is needed because the canonical sources are unambiguous. Option A preserves validate()'s pure-function signature without threading a fromMigration parameter, at the cost of a non-SPEC implementation-internal field in the document object. The developer documented this trade-off and flagged the non-SPEC field as a future concern.\n\n**SPEC \u00c2\u00a710.3\u00e2\u20ac\u201c10.5 conformance:** \u00c2\u00a710.3 function signature implemented correctly (migrate(doc, targetVersion) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 {document, migrationReport} or {error}). \u00c2\u00a710.4 two-leg chain (v0.2\u00e2\u2020\u2019v0.3\u00e2\u2020\u2019v0.4) is fully implemented with the six mandated v0.3\u00e2\u2020\u2019v0.4 transforms (specVersion, @context via VMP_CONTEXT, type array, iao:isAbout init, ecm:serializations init, LEGACY_REALIST_ANCHOR_PLACEHOLDER emission) and four mandated v0.2\u00e2\u2020\u2019v0.3 transforms (specVersion, literalAssertions, settings defaults, subclass/subproperty stubs). \u00c2\u00a710.5 (snapshot migration) is cited in IMPL PLAN SPEC refs but has no corresponding AC in the five enumerated ACs; the developer treats it as deferred and this is consistent with the task scope.\n\n**All 5 ACs covered:** AC1 (v0.2\u00e2\u2020\u2019v0.4 output has correct specVersion and iao:isAbout) \u00e2\u0153\u201c. AC2 (v0.3\u00e2\u2020\u2019v0.4 + validate() = zero hard errors, exactly one LEGACY_REALIST_ANCHOR_PLACEHOLDER info finding; ft-097 resolved) \u00e2\u0153\u201c. AC3 (migration report enumerates all 5 changed fields: type, iao:isAbout, ecm:specVersion, ecm:serializations, @context) \u00e2\u0153\u201c \u00e2\u20ac\u201d note: the ecm:serializations count depends on V03_FIXTURE not having the field pre-existing; the test passes on the fixture as authored; the conditional add logic is correct per the SPEC's 'initializes' language. AC4 (byte-identical golden file) DEFERRED per OED-306 with a named pass-stub in the test file \u00e2\u0153\u201c. AC5 (v0.5 input returns INVALID_SPEC_VERSION error; document and migrationReport are null) \u00e2\u0153\u201c.\n\n**INVALID_SPEC_VERSION error handling:** migrate() returns {document: null, migrationReport: null, error: {code, message}} for forward-version inputs \u00e2\u20ac\u201d this discriminated union shape resolves recon open question 4 (return envelope shape not specified in SPEC or IMPL PLAN). The detection gate matches the existing validate() logic (MAX_MAJOR=0, MAX_MINOR=4). The targetVersion guard for unsupported targets (non-'0.4') returns the same error code \u00e2\u20ac\u201d a defensive addition consistent with AC5's spirit.\n\n**Kernel purity / layer boundaries:** src/migrate/index.ts imports VMP_CONTEXT from src/kernel/canonicalize.js (Layer 0 to Layer 0-adjacent read; not a Layer 0 self-referential import; purity checker only scans src/kernel/). Imports from src/validate/codes.js (constants only). No import from src/adapters/ or src/composition/. No Date.now(), Math.random(), or non-deterministic APIs. Pure function declaration is structurally consistent.\n\n**Open items not blocking ratification:** (1) LEGACY_DOCUMENT_MIGRATED is not emitted by this change \u00e2\u20ac\u201d AC1-AC5 do not require it, and the developer's C5 comment explicitly marks it as '(remaining)'. (2) The SPEC \u00c2\u00a717.1/\u00c2\u00a717.4 severity taxonomy contradiction (info finding that blocks export) is unresolved in DECISIONS.md; the implementation correctly defers export-blocking to the adapter layer and emits ecm:info severity as declared in codes.ts. (3) FR-C013 gap (no FR-C covering v0.3\u00e2\u2020\u2019v0.4 leg) is a SPEC coverage gap, not an implementation gap \u00e2\u20ac\u201d not blocking for this change.\n\n**Test file conformance:** tests/legacy-migration.test.ts follows the established hand-rolled pattern (node:assert, console PASS/FAIL with \u00e2\u0153\u201c/\u00e2\u0153\u2014, process.exit(1) on failure, inline fixtures with no on-disk fixture reads) confirmed by recon F13. The two additional tests recommended by the developer (marker-absent regression guard, validate() regression for placeholder-only without marker) are advisory and do not affect the ruling.",
