        "bankings": [
          {
            "id": "B1",
            "category": "pattern-observation",
            "content": "ft-097-test-validator-3 resolution established a pattern for handling mutually-exclusive findings that arise from migration provenance: when SPEC uses exclusive-disjunction language ('MISSING_REALIST_ANCHOR or LEGACY_REALIST_ANCHOR_PLACEHOLDER') and an IMPL PLAN AC directly prohibits co-emission, an in-document provenance marker (ecm:_legacyAnchorPlaceholder: true) is a clean Option A resolution that preserves validate()'s pure-function signature without threading provenance as a call-site parameter. The trade-off is that the marker is a non-SPEC implementation artifact in the document object; future serialization or export work must decide whether to strip it. The canonical basis was sufficient to close the forward-track without a new ADR."
          },
          {
            "id": "B2",
            "category": "pattern-observation",
            "content": "AC4 (golden file, blocked on OED-306 closure) is handled in the test file via a named pass-stub with the blocking condition cited inline rather than a skipped or absent test. This deferred-AC-stub pattern creates a traceable coverage entry that survives into the test suite output \u00e2\u20ac\u201d a passing test with documented deferral reason \u00e2\u20ac\u201d preventing silent AC omission while avoiding a false failure. The same pattern was observed in tests/vmp-serializer.test.ts (referenced in C6 rationale); it is now a cross-task pattern candidate for the project's testing discipline."
          },
          {
            "id": "B3",
            "category": "methodology-refinement-candidate",
            "content": "The proposed change defers LEGACY_DOCUMENT_MIGRATED (the second task-1.9 info code) because the five enumerated ACs do not require its emission. The developer updated the TODO comment to distinguish 'implemented' from 'remaining' within the same task scope. This surfaces a methodology candidate: when a task's SPEC refs include codes that are not covered by any AC, the developer should either add an AC gap note to the IMPL PLAN or explicitly flag the code as deferred-to-follow-up in the change rationale. The current C5 comment update is the right mechanism but only visible in the diff \u00e2\u20ac\u201d an explicit open_question entry would have made it more visible to downstream consumers of the change."
          }
