      "@id": "urn:fnsr:task:138-recon-normalize-on-load",
      "agent": "reconnaissance",
      "status": "done",
      "attempts": 1,
      "outputs": {
        "findings": [
          {
            "id": "F1",
            "claim": "SPEC.md \u00c2\u00a75.3 defines the normalization trigger: if a file is loaded that is not in canonical form, the system normalizes it to canonical form on save and reports the normalization.",
            "evidence": [
              {
                "file": "project/SPEC.md",
                "lines": "338-339",
                "excerpt": "A \"lossless round-trip\" means: `serialize(parse(file)) == file` bytewise, where `file` is already in canonical form. If a file is loaded that is not in canonical form, the system normalizes it to canonical form on save and reports the normalization."
              }
            ],
            "kind": "observation"
          },
          {
            "id": "F2",
            "claim": "FR-C014 is the functional requirement binding the normalizeOnLoad feature: 'Normalize loaded non-canonical documents to canonical form (\u00c2\u00a75.3).'",
            "evidence": [
              {
                "file": "project/SPEC.md",
                "lines": "1314",
                "excerpt": "| FR-C014 | Normalize loaded non-canonical documents to canonical form (\u00c2\u00a75.3). |"
              }
            ],
            "kind": "observation"
          },
          {
            "id": "F3",
            "claim": "IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md \u00c2\u00a71.10 specifies the function signature `normalizeOnLoad(doc): {document, wasNormalized}`, the condition for `wasNormalized: true` (bytewise difference between canonical serializer output and input), and the downstream consequence (validate() emits NORMALIZED_ON_SAVE info finding when wasNormalized is true).",
            "evidence": [
              {
                "file": "project/IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md",
                "lines": "209-221",
                "excerpt": "**Sub-tasks:**\n- Implement `normalizeOnLoad(doc): {document, wasNormalized}`. If canonical serializer output differs bytewise from input, set `wasNormalized: true`.\n- When `wasNormalized: true`, `validate()` emits `NORMALIZED_ON_SAVE` info finding.\n\n**Acceptance criteria:**\n- Calling `normalizeOnLoad` twice: second call returns `wasNormalized: false`. Verified by unit test.\n- A non-canonically-ordered valid fixture returns `wasNormalized: true` on first call. Verified by unit test.\n- `NORMALIZED_ON_SAVE` present in `validate()` output when and only when `wasNormalized` was true. Verified by unit test."
              }
            ],
            "kind": "observation"
          },
          {
            "id": "F4",
            "claim": "The developer task (urn:fnsr:task:139-dev-normalize-on-load) designates `src/normalize/index.ts` as the intended module location for normalizeOnLoad.",
            "evidence": [
              {
                "file": "phase1-task-1-10-chain.json",
                "lines": "46",
                "excerpt": "\"Place in src/normalize/index.ts (new module).\""
              }
            ],
            "kind": "observation"
          },
          {
            "id": "F5",
            "claim": "`src/normalize/` does not currently exist as a directory; no `normalize` module exists anywhere under `src/`.",
            "evidence": [
              {
                "file": "src",
                "lines": "N/A",
                "excerpt": "Glob pattern `src/**/*.ts` returns: src/kernel/index.ts, src/kernel/transform.ts, src/kernel/canonicalize.ts, src/tbox/index.ts, src/validate/codes.ts, src/projection/index.ts, src/emit/n-triples.ts, src/emit/triple-narration.ts, src/emit/turtle.ts, src/iri/index.ts, src/refactor/index.ts, src/manifest/index.ts, src/migrate/index.ts, src/validate/index.ts \u00e2\u20ac\u201d no normalize module present."
              }
            ],
            "kind": "observation"
          },
          {
            "id": "F6",
            "claim": "`serializeVmp(project: Record<string, unknown>): string` is fully implemented in `src/kernel/canonicalize.ts` and is the designated consumer for normalizeOnLoad; it accepts a parsed JS object and returns the canonical UTF-8 string ending with a single LF.",
            "evidence": [
              {
                "file": "src/kernel/canonicalize.ts",
                "lines": "248-267",
                "excerpt": "export function serializeVmp(project: Record<string, unknown>): string {\n  // Pass 1: compact aliases (@id\u00e2\u2020\u2019id, @type\u00e2\u2020\u2019type) + timestamp normalization\n  const aliased = applyAliases(project) as Record<string, unknown>;\n  ...\n  return JSON.stringify(canonical, null, 2) + \"\\n\";\n}"
              }
            ],
            "kind": "observation"
          },
          {
            "id": "F7",
            "claim": "`serializeVmp` is idempotent: `serializeVmp(JSON.parse(serializeVmp(doc)))` equals `serializeVmp(doc)` bytewise for any VMP project document, per its JSDoc and confirmed by tests/vmp-serializer.test.ts AC2.",
            "evidence": [
              {
                "file": "src/kernel/canonicalize.ts",
                "lines": "242-244",
                "excerpt": "* Idempotent: `serializeVmp(JSON.parse(serializeVmp(doc)))` equals\n * `serializeVmp(doc)` bytewise for any VMP project document."
              },
              {
                "file": "tests/vmp-serializer.test.ts",
                "lines": "200-217",
                "excerpt": "// AC2: idempotency \u00e2\u20ac\u201d serialize(parse(serialize(doc))) === serialize(doc)\ntry {\n  const s1 = serializeVmp(MINIMAL_VMP_ATID);\n  const s2 = serializeVmp(JSON.parse(s1) as Record<string, unknown>);\n  strictEqual(s2, s1);\n  pass(\"serializeVmp idempotent on @id/@type input (AC2)\");\n}"
              }
            ],
            "kind": "observation"
          },
          {
            "id": "F8",
            "claim": "`NORMALIZED_ON_SAVE` is already declared as a string constant in `src/validate/codes.ts` with a comment pointing to task 1.10, but it is not yet imported or emitted in `src/validate/index.ts`.",
            "evidence": [
              {
                "file": "src/validate/codes.ts",
                "lines": "54",
                "excerpt": "export const NORMALIZED_ON_SAVE                = \"NORMALIZED_ON_SAVE\";                // emitted by task 1.10"
              },
              {
                "file": "src/validate/index.ts",
                "lines": "12-16",
                "excerpt": "import {\n  MISSING_REALIST_ANCHOR,\n  INVALID_SPEC_VERSION,\n  LEGACY_REALIST_ANCHOR_PLACEHOLDER,\n} from \"./codes.js\";"
              },
              {
                "file": "src/validate/index.ts",
                "lines": "203",
                "excerpt": "  // NORMALIZED_ON_SAVE -> task 1.10."
              }
            ],
            "kind": "observation"
          },
          {
            "id": "F9",
            "claim": "The established precedent for passing context from a pre-validate processing step into `validate()` is a hidden marker field on the document object itself: `src/migrate/index.ts` sets `ecm:_legacyAnchorPlaceholder: true` on the migrated document, and `src/validate/index.ts` reads `project[\"ecm:_legacyAnchorPlaceholder\"] === true` to decide which finding to emit.",
            "evidence": [
              {
                "file": "src/migrate/index.ts",
                "lines": "204",
                "excerpt": "  result[\"ecm:_legacyAnchorPlaceholder\"] = true;"
              },
              {
                "file": "src/validate/index.ts",
                "lines": "142-143",
                "excerpt": "  const isLegacyAnchorPlaceholder =\n    project[\"ecm:_legacyAnchorPlaceholder\"] === true;"
              }
            ],
            "kind": "observation"
          },
          {
            "id": "F10",
            "claim": "The developer task input directions for task 1.10 explicitly describe the marker mechanism as: 'Decide marker mechanism: ecm:_wasNormalizedOnLoad flag on doc (similar to gap-9 resolution pattern from task 1.9 if applicable), or a separate stateful parameter,' confirming both options are under consideration.",
            "evidence": [
              {
                "file": "phase1-task-1-10-chain.json",
                "lines": "44",
                "excerpt": "\"When wasNormalized=true, the validator MUST emit NORMALIZED_ON_SAVE info finding. Decide marker mechanism: ecm:_wasNormalizedOnLoad flag on doc (similar to gap-9 resolution pattern from task 1.9 if applicable), or a separate stateful parameter.\""
              }
            ],
            "kind": "observation"
          },
          {
            "id": "F11",
            "claim": "SPEC.md \u00c2\u00a717.4 classifies `NORMALIZED_ON_SAVE` as an info finding with the description 'The loaded project was not in canonical form; it was normalized on save.'",
            "evidence": [
              {
                "file": "project/SPEC.md",
                "lines": "1279",
                "excerpt": "| `NORMALIZED_ON_SAVE` | The loaded project was not in canonical form; it was normalized on save. |"
              }
            ],
            "kind": "observation"
          },
          {
            "id": "F12",
            "claim": "The IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md sub-task says 'If canonical serializer output differs bytewise from input' but the stated signature is `normalizeOnLoad(doc)` taking a single parsed-object parameter; a parsed JS object does not retain the original file's byte content (whitespace, BOM, CRLF), so byte-level comparison against the original file is structurally impossible without the raw string.",
            "evidence": [
              {
                "file": "project/IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md",
                "lines": "214",
                "excerpt": "- Implement `normalizeOnLoad(doc): {document, wasNormalized}`. If canonical serializer output differs bytewise from input, set `wasNormalized: true`."
              },
              {
                "file": "phase1-task-1-10-chain.json",
                "lines": "43",
                "excerpt": "\"normalizeOnLoad(doc): {document, wasNormalized}. Calls serializeVmp; compares bytes against input; wasNormalized = (output bytes differ).\""
              }
            ],
            "kind": "inference"
          },
          {
            "id": "F13",
            "claim": "The idempotency property of `serializeVmp` \u00e2\u20ac\u201d combined with V8/Node.js preserving JSON.parse insertion order \u00e2\u20ac\u201d makes it feasible to detect non-canonical structure by comparing `serializeVmp(doc)` against `JSON.stringify(doc, null, 2) + '\\n'` when `doc` is a freshly parsed JS object. Non-canonical key ordering, array ordering, and non-normalized timestamps would be detected; original-file BOM and CRLF differences would not.",
            "evidence": [
              {
                "file": "src/kernel/canonicalize.ts",
                "lines": "265-267",
                "excerpt": "// \u00c2\u00a75.3 rules 6\u00e2\u20ac\u201d7: two-space indent; JSON.stringify always uses \\n for newlines\n// (string literal semantics, platform-independent); one terminating newline.\nreturn JSON.stringify(canonical, null, 2) + \"\\n\";"
              },
              {
                "file": "tests/vmp-serializer.test.ts",
                "lines": "59-80",
                "excerpt": "const UNORDERED_VMP: Record<string, unknown> = {\n  \"id\": \"urn:uuid:...\",\n  \"type\": [\"iao:OntologyDesignPattern\", \"ecm:Project\"],  // reversed\n  ...  // non-canonical ordering preserved in JS object literal"
              }
            ],
            "kind": "inference"
          },
          {
            "id": "F14",
            "claim": "The Phase 2 task 2.1 call chain (`migrate() + normalizeOnLoad() + validate()` on file open) implies that `normalizeOnLoad` receives a parsed JS object (the migrate() result) rather than a raw file string, confirming the parsed-object input pattern.",
            "evidence": [
              {
                "file": "project/IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md",
                "lines": "309",
                "excerpt": "- FR-U002 Open project: `<input type=\"file\">`, calls `migrate()` + `normalizeOnLoad()` + `validate()`, shows FR-U029 migration notice if migrated."
              }
            ],
            "kind": "observation"
          },
          {
