          }
        ],
        "open_questions": [
          "TypeScript compilation of src/cli/index.ts: the `parseArgs` return type with @types/node ^22.0.0 uses complex conditional types. Two specific areas need build verification: (1) definite-assignment of `content: string` in cmdExport after the switch (process.exit() returns never in the non-assigning cases -- TypeScript 5.x should track this); (2) definite-assignment of `raw: string` in readJsonFile after try-catch where the catch calls process.exit() (never). If TypeScript reports 'variable used before assignment', the fix is to add a non-null assertion or restructure with a helper. Run `npm run build` after applying.",
          "TypeScript: `values[\"allow-outside-cwd\"]` access. With `{ type: 'boolean' as const, default: false }`, TypeScript should infer the type as `boolean` (not `boolean | undefined`). If the compiler infers a wider type, cast with `values[\"allow-outside-cwd\"] as boolean`.",
          "TypeScript: `values.old` and `values[\"new\"]` access. The key `\"new\"` is a reserved word; bracket-notation access `values[\"new\"]` is valid TypeScript. If the compiler rejects dot-notation `values.new` anywhere, change to bracket notation.",
          "Reconnaissance open question (F8): SPEC section 23 defines exit code 2 as 'file I/O errors'; IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN section 1.11 and ADR-003 use exit code 2 for three meanings (path escape, not-implemented, file I/O). This proposal follows the IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN/ADR-003 broadened interpretation. If the operator wants SPEC section 23 updated to enumerate all three uses, that is a separate editorial-correction chain.",
          "Reconnaissance open question (Q3): export --format turtle golden-file AC is deferred (OED-306 and OED-313 open). The integration test (C4) substitutes a structural assertion (@prefix in stdout). When OED-306 and OED-313 close, the operator should queue a follow-up chain to commit test/golden/graph.ttl and replace the structural assertion with a byte-identical comparison.",
          "Reconnaissance open question (Q4): path containment applies to input file paths in this proposal. The --out output path also passes through safeResolve (same containment logic). If the operator intended output paths to have different containment rules, surface as a follow-up question.",
          "Chain 2 deferred scope: export --format json-ld (full implementation), export --format mermaid (full implementation + src/emit/mermaid.ts), and integration test polish. These are stubbed in C2 with exit 2 + 'not yet implemented' messages.",
          "The .cli-test-fixtures/ temp directory is created in the project root during test runs and removed in the finally block. Developers running tests repeatedly should confirm the directory is absent between runs (teardown is always called). Consider adding .cli-test-fixtures/ to .gitignore if it is not already excluded."
        ],
        "summary": "Chain 1 of the IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN section 1.11 CLI surface. Four changes: (C1) new src/emit/markdown.ts -- pure markdown emitter using FR-C008 triple narration; (C2) new src/cli/index.ts -- full validate/export(turtle+n-triples+markdown)/migrate/refactor-iri commands plus import-ontology and export-zip Phase 1 stubs (exit 2 + exact ADR-003 stderr), path containment per SPEC section 12.2, util.parseArgs Node 22 built-in, adapter-tier layer discipline preserved; (C3) package.json bin field adding 'graphwrite': 'dist/cli/index.js'; (C4) new tests/cli-integration.test.ts covering all 8 phase-1-reachable ACs via subprocess spawn. Scope-split decision: Chain 1 delivers validate, export (turtle/n-triples/markdown), migrate, refactor-iri, path containment, and stubs. Chain 2 defers export --format json-ld (full), export --format mermaid (full + src/emit/mermaid.ts), and golden-file ACs (blocked on OED-306/OED-313). The TypeScript purity checker (npm run test:purity) is not affected since src/cli/ is adapter-tier and not scanned by scripts/ensure-kernel-purity.ts.",
        "self_assessment": "uncertain"
