        "open_questions": [
          "SCOPE-SPLIT DECISION (documented per operator instruction): This dispatch implements the first safe chain only \u00e2\u20ac\u201d fast-check devDep (C1) + canonical idempotency PBT (C2+C3) + 3 minimal fixtures (C4+C5+C6). The three remaining property-test rewrites are deferred to a follow-up chain: (a) cascade reversibility in tests/iri-refactor.test.ts AC3 (currently hand-rolled Mulberry32, 50 samples); (b) cascade idempotency in tests/iri-refactor.test.ts AC4 (currently hand-rolled Mulberry32, 50 samples); (c) semantic-projection stability in tests/semantic-projection.test.ts AC3 (currently hand-rolled Mulberry32, 50 samples). Those three files already pass their ACs \u00e2\u20ac\u201d the rewrite is additive quality improvement, not a blocking gap. Operator should queue a follow-up chain for those three files after this chain lands and npm test is green.",
          "ADR for framework decision: Reconnaissance F9 notes no ADR records the 'keep hand-rolled vs migrate to Vitest/Jest' decision. IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN section 1.12 still mandates 'Configure Vitest/Jest'. The operator-cited defaults override this for task 1.12, but the override is not captured in DECISIONS.md. Should ADR-007 be queued to record this decision before Phase 1 exit gate review? Without an ADR, the Phase 1 exit gate (item 1: 'npm test zero failures') is achievable but the Vitest/Jest mandate in IMPL_PLAN section 1.12 remains a dormant conflict.",
          "Applier BOM behavior on new .jsonld files: CLAUDE.md applier description mentions 'UTF-8 BOM on new files'. The VMP canonical format requires UTF-8 no-BOM (SPEC section 5.3 rule 7). C4, C5, C6 are new .jsonld files. Operator should verify the applier does NOT add a BOM to these files; if it does, the byte-comparison fixture test (once OED-306+OED-313 close) will fail.",
          "fast-check module resolution under NodeNext: tsconfig.test.json extends tsconfig.json which uses 'moduleResolution: NodeNext'. fast-check v3 publishes proper ESM exports. If 'npm i --save-dev fast-check' installs a version that lacks a valid exports field for NodeNext resolution, TypeScript will error on 'import * as fc from fast-check'. Mitigation: if compile fails, check fast-check version and pin to >=3.0.0 which ships full ESM support.",
          "OED-307 closure: Reconnaissance F8 notes that cli-integration.test.ts (task 1.11) satisfies OED-307's gated work, but the OED tracking table still records OED-307 as Open. Should OED-307 be formally closed in IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md as a separate editorial task before Phase 1 exit gate? Not blocking for task 1.12 but leaves a stale Open entry in the OED table.",
          "Coverage tooling (AC5 of section 1.12 / SPEC section 21.2): Reconnaissance F5 confirms no coverage tooling present. Per operator_cited_defaults this is deferred. This means section 1.12's AC5 ('Coverage >= 85%') and Phase 1 exit gate item 9 remain open. If Phase 1 exit gate review treats AC5 as non-blocking (gated on CI tooling phase), no action needed now. Operator should confirm Phase 1 can close without AC5 before marking 1.12 done."
        ],
        "summary": "SCOPE-SPLIT applied per operator_cited_defaults + scope_warning guidance. This chain lands the minimum to make the 4th property-based invariant (canonical idempotency) fast-check compliant and adds 3 fixture files. Specifically: C1 adds fast-check ^3.0.0 to devDependencies (operator runs 'npm i --save-dev fast-check' post-applier); C2 removes the deferred note from vmp-serializer.test.ts header and adds 'import * as fc from fast-check'; C3 inserts the AC2-PBT block (100 samples, seed 0xcafef00d) that exercises timestamp normalization variants, named-array ordering, and IRI-array ordering before the existing Summary section; C4 creates test/fixtures/canonical-v0.4/minimal.jsonld with full VMP_CONTEXT in canonical key order; C5 creates test/fixtures/malformed/missing-realist-anchor.jsonld; C6 creates test/fixtures/malformed/invalid-spec-version.jsonld. Deferred to follow-up chain: rewrites of the 3 already-passing hand-rolled property tests in tests/iri-refactor.test.ts (AC3 reversibility, AC4 idempotency) and tests/semantic-projection.test.ts (AC3 canvas-layout-invariance). Those already pass at 50 samples; migration to fast-check is additive. Also deferred: comprehensive fixture set (all 16 section 17.2 codes), golden files, deterministic CI job, coverage tooling \u00e2\u20ac\u201d all remain gated on OED-306+OED-313 and CI-infrastructure phase per operator defaults.",
